body:

I feel like this will wreck havoc on me later.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Joltik and Galvantula
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Joltik and Galvantula
body:
595: Joltik

Sad spider fans got treated to a Pokemon that may have been a little dissatisfaction, just by proxy of Spinarak and Ariados being some of Gen 2’s throwaway fodder Pokemon. While cool, one only kind of looked like a spider and is otherwise pretty basic. Fast forward to 10+ years later, and we finally receive a second spider Pokemon; the ever so loved Joltik.

At the time, Joltik was the single tiniest Pokemon in the entire Pokedex, standing at only 4 inches tall. And so far, Pokemon have only ever been tied with it in size. What’s more, one of the fun aspects of this Pokemon is that, just like the “tik” bit of its name implies, it’s a parasite. It’ll latch onto sources of electricity to feast on them. Which is all the more cute when you try to imagine these things as house pests. Electricity acting wonky, so you go and look at your wall socket to see what’s up, only to spot one of these little guys sucking energy out of it. And it’s too damn adorable for you to ever think about hurting it.

I also love that Joltik looks to be modeled after a the teeny tiny jumping spider. One of the cutest spiders out there. Perfectly mimicking their huge puppy-dog eyes, and a lot of Joltik in motion likes to portray the little friend as a really jumpy fellow.

Personal Score: 9/10

Joltik has too much power.

596: Galvantula

I love spiders. And this. Now THIS is a spider!! And I think its great that we have an official tarantula Pokemon that is fluffy, cute, and still cool all at the same time. And on top of that, is keeping all the lovely things about spiders. So many eyes! Covered in fuzz, like a real tarantula! While it may lacks some legs, it’s even got a pair of pedipalps!

And it’s even great fun in its typing to date. Been waiting for a Bug/Electric type, and I’m glad our first one is a real winner. And I’m happy it’s a spider too. It’s a bug you wouldn’t have expected to have turned into a Bug/Electric type, especially not as a series first. With so many bioluminescent bugs running around, any one of them could’ve predictably wound up being Electric type. But it’s a web-slinging spider that gets the honors! A spider with electrified webbing is simply such a fun idea, I’m surprised something like that didn’t come around sooner in the series.

Personal Score: 10/10

Flawless spider friends

Overall:

I love them both. So so much.

[Archive]

summary: Ultra Sun/Ultra Moon Competition - Let’s Go! Cup
title: Ultra Sun/Ultra Moon Competition - Let’s Go! Cup
body:
It has been announced that the next online competition is the Let’s Go! Cup, which only allows the use of Pikachu and Eevee. No item restrictions or generation restrictions, so bring on your gimmicky sets! You are allowed one Pokemon, so choose your favorite!

The most used of the pair will have a mobile wallpaper distributed to participants. No other rewards.
